HEADWORD: Cascalho
<hw>Cas*cal"ho</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg., a chip of
stone, gravel.]</ety> <def>A deposit of pebbles, gravel, and ferruginous
sand, in which the Brazilian diamond is usually found.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

